      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 814: The audio-triggered bitrate reduction intentionally avoids clamping to `videoBitrateMin`, so repeated congestion callbacks can drive the video bitrate to zero or an unusably low value. That can effectively kill video and may pass invalid values to encoder/restart logic. Keep the reduction one-way, but clamp to a safe lower bound such as the configured minimum bitrate.\\n```suggestion\\n        newBitrate \u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned int\u003e(std::lround(static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(oldBitrate) * reductionFactor));\\n        newBitrate \u003d std::max(videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMin, std::min(newBitrate, oldBitrate));\\n```",
      "revId": "25fa909d52da252700c462df2c5cfd18434d333e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
