      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 233: The congestion callback captures the call and audio session, but it is never cleared when the audio RTP session is detached/reconfigured. If the session object outlives the call media association, the callback can continue walking call state from the RTCP thread and coupling unrelated future media sessions. Clear the callback when tearing down or replacing audio RTP sessions, or bind it to the same lifecycle mechanism used for voice callbacks.",
      "revId": "25fa909d52da252700c462df2c5cfd18434d333e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
